OL,3,CWales' poverty crisis deepening with
OL,4,C'little progress' in 20 years, report
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FAccording to the 'Poverty in Wales'
OL,8,Freport, published on Tuesday, more
OL,9,Fthan 1 in 5 people in Wales (22%) `
OL,10,Fwhich is around 700,000 people ` are
OL,11,Fliving in poverty.
OL,13,FOf these, 400,000 are working-age
OL,14,Fadults (21%), 200,000 are children
OL,15,F(31%) and 100,000 are pensioners (16%).
OL,17,FThe report warns that if no action is
OL,18,Ftaken, child poverty in Wales could
OL,19,Freach 34% by 2029-30, which would make
OL,20,Fit the highest rate of all UK nations.
