OL,3,CWales' poverty crisis deepening with
OL,4,C'little progress' in 20 years, report
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FThe highest child poverty rates by
OL,8,Flocal authority are Blaenau Gwent
OL,9,F(34%), Merthyr Tydfil, Ceredigion and
OL,10,FNewport (32%), and the Isle of
OL,11,FAnglesey and Pembrokeshire (31%).
OL,13,FThe Welsh Government says it is
OL,14,Fdetermined to do all it can to prevent
OL,15,Fpeople from going into poverty and to
OL,16,Fhelp those who need support the most.
OL,18,FThe findings also reveal that nearly
OL,19,Fhalf a million people in Wales lived
OL,20,Fin deep poverty in 2020-23, with
OL,21,F310,000 in very deep poverty.
